HEADWORD: Conclamation
<hw>Con`cla*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>conclamatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>An outcry or shout of many
together.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Before his funeral <qex>conclamation</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>May
(Lucan).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

